Experiencing mild respiratory symptoms? Chances are you probably have rhinovirus, otherwise known as the common cold, but it's important you get a COVID-19 test just to be safe. 

The main symptoms of the Rhinovirus are:
- Sneezing
- A mild temperature (38.3°C–38.9°C)
- Headaches
- Sore throat
- Cough

The symptoms of rhinovirus manifest in a similar way to COVID, so if you or a family member has any of these symptoms, you should be tested for COVID-19.

Talk to us @bondidoctors if you have any questions. Book online or call us to book a telehealth consult.

A glimpse into my next two projects. We are traveling today for my next shows opening September 17 at CCB in Lisbon and September 25 at Forum MAIA in Porto and am so grateful for the time I had here at Mother Mandala at the international Forest Art biennale. @pepe_de_sein photographed and was very important in the whole process. The exchange with the other artists was amazing. Ute Ritschel the curator of the show organized another amazing Forest art path that will be seen by min 100 000 people or more. In china and korea the art paths that she curated were seen by millions!  Albrecht Haag and Lukas Einsele were super supportive here during the residency together with their team...

HEALTHY BONES ACTION WEEK -17-23 AUGUST⁠
⁠
HOW DO I GET ENOUGH CALCIUM FOR BONE HEALTH?⁠
⁠
The top 3 sources of calcium in the Australian diet are:⁠
? Milk;⁠
? Cheese; and⁠
? Yoghurt.⁠
⁠
Calcium can also be found in non-dairy food options, such as:⁠
? Alternative milks, such as soy and almond milks, with 100mg calcium per 100ml;⁠
? Leafy green vegetables, such as broccoli, mustard cabbage, Bok Choy, silverbeet, cucumber, celery and chick peas;⁠
? Canned fish with soft edible bones, such as sardines or salmon;⁠
? Almonds, dried figs and dried apricots; and ⁠
? Tofu. ⁠
⁠
Calcium Requirements change over our lifespan:⁠
? Children (1 - 3 years) = 500mg per day⁠
? Children (4 - 8 years) = 700mg per day⁠
? Girls and Boys (9 - 11 years) = 1000mg per day⁠
??‍?? Teenagers (12 - 18 years) = 1300mg per day⁠
? Adults (19+ years) = 1000mg per day⁠
?? Women (50+ years) = 1300mg per day⁠
?? Men (70+ years) = 1300mg per day⁠
